quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “O deniers,"
  109,2,"I do not worship what you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>worship,"
  109,3,"nor do you worship what I worship,"
  109,4,"nor shall I ever worship what you worship,"
  109,5,"nor shall you ever worship what I worship—"
  109,6,"you have your religion, and I have my religion{1}.”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is deen which means ‘a way of life’, ‘religion’ or ‘recompense’.
  110,1,"When there comes Allah’s support and the conquest,"
  110,2,"and you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>see mankind entering Allah’s religion in crowds,"
  110,3,"then highly exalt your Lord with praise and seek His forgiveness; indeed, He has always been Granting and Accepting of repentance."
  111,1,"May the hands of Abi Lahab{1}be ruined, and may he be ruined!",footnotes:1:The uncle of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), and one of his fiercest enemies.
  111,2,"His wealth did{1}not avail him, nor did what he earned.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  111,3,"He will roast in a flaming fire,"
  111,4,"while his wife{1}, <span class=""h"">that firewood carrier<sup foot_note=""81505"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>—",footnotes:1:Abu Lahab’s wife who used to throw thorns in the way of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him).
  111,5,"around her neck is a rope of palm fiber."
